name: Ulu Petanu Waterfall
address: manik sawang, Jl. Raya Bayad, Kedisan, Kec. Tegallalang, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80561, Indonesia
review 1: Really cool waterfall! The water is nice and it‚Äôs quite expansive. We hiked a bit and found two main waterfalls, one mini waterfall, pig farm, and a cave. I recommend going early in the morning as we got here at 9:30 am and it got busy fast. For 20k rupiah, it was pretty awesome!
review 2:
Beautiful waterfall which is fairly newly opened to tourists I believe. Clean toilets, small stand selling drinks, not too many steps down (and then up on the way back!) and a well trodden path which wasn't dangerous at all in my opinion.
The water, as expected, was very cold! But some lovely photos!
review 3:
It‚Äôs not the biggest waterfall around this area and  also not the busiest

If you want to swim, you have to go through some rocks to get in the water, for me, it didn‚Äôt feel very inviting so I decided against swimming ü§î

Entrance cost around 20K
review 4: Another beautiful waterfall in Bali. Not difficult to reach, from the parking lot it only takes about 5 minutes to get down. There is koi pond, and if you hike a little bit you can see another waterfall. The bridge need to repair for safety reason. Ticket price only 20k/person. Better go on weekday, cause on weekend it can be so crowded
review 5:
The waterfall is beautiful. there is less crowd. The water still has blue color and there are some koi fish swim around. THE MOST IMPORTANT IS THE ACCESS TO THE WATERFALL. It‚Äôs so easy and not far away from the ticket counter. For local, the ticket price is 20k Rupiah and for tourists is 30k Rupiah. You can also get free coffee after your visit to the waterfall. The coffee counter is in front of the ticket counter. There is no chair or place to put your belongings while swimming, though. However, there‚Äôs some rock to put your belongings. In google map, it said to be open until 5 pm, but I came at a quarter to 5 pm and they still let me in. They said, they open until 6 pm for visitors that came before 5 pm.

If you go straight from the waterfall, there‚Äôs a jungle track. I don‚Äôt know what you can find in the end of the track, because, when I was there, it was raining. I suggested you to not explore the track while rain because it‚Äôs quite slippery and dangerous (you can fall to the river). STAY SAFE!

name: The Amertha Restaurant
address: Jl. Sentanu, Tampaksiring, Kec. Tampaksiring, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1: A bit expensive, the taste is not very good, the food is cold not warm.  The plates are big and the portions are small.  Friendly service, a bit chaotic on weekends
review 2: We were four peole and we all think the food was not good at all. We all took chicken, but it was too dry and we didn‚Äôt eat much. Then there was also one long hair in riceüò≥ Service was okey, nothing bad to say about it.
review 3:
Lovely place and settings. Staff are friendly and attentive.

Food wise is mixed feelings, some are good some are mediocre. The one that I have was rather "lack in flavour", my friend said his was good.
review 4: One of the best restaurants in Bali that we‚Äôve ever tried. The food is fabulous, the staff is accommodating, and the ambiance is so refreshing. We‚Äôll definitely come back. Keep up the good work. ‚ù§Ô∏è
review 5:
Very good customer service , cool vibe .
The food was surprisingly tasty and good.  I had crispy chicken any my husband fish with balenese sauce , a young coconut and a mixed juice.
Keep up with the good work and service !

name: Warung Pondok Bali
address: Jl. Sentanu No.4, Tampaksiring, Kecamatan Ubud, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1: Food was ok. Friendly staff. Reasonable price. Nice view
review 2: Recommended by a local at the Pura Tirta Empul I went to have brekkie and was really good. Tasty omelette and fresh watermelon juice. Nice place just maybe too close to the main road but the view to the rice fields are great!
review 3: Good food and friendly staff. Card payment available. The view from the restaurant towards the rice field was beautiful!
review 4: Great place to chill and have authentic Balinese cuisine!
review 5: Very close to the temple and much more reasonably priced then some of the other places we saw prior to attending. You can eat with a view over the local rice paddy, you are right next to a busy road mind. The juice was proper fresh, but of fruit and no added sugar proves that fact.

name: TAMAN APIS CARANA
address: H8P4+9CH, Tampaksiring, Gianyar Regency, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1: Great camping spot. Lovely locals take good care of you and provide excellent service. Beautiful tracks to discover... I had our teepee first time up in this place. Our plan is to produce more teepees, so you can enjoy camping in totally new level. Tell me if you are interested.

name: Paras Petanu Ground village
address: Kedisan, Tegallalang, Gianyar Regency, Bali 80561, Indonesia
review 1: Great place to camp, with a beautiful view. Which are awesome waterfall, river, forest, etc.  So if you have any plan to camp, you have to consider this place on your list
review 2: Awesome!!! If you need to take yourself for a weekend camp, this is one of the best place to go. With the signature of Balinese hospitality and fresh air from the woods will fill you with positive energy. They also offered some outdoor activities like : trekking, tubing, and sometimes slack line. The trek itself is a route that follows the Petanu river, against the stream, that ended at the hidden waterfall. The way back to the camp ground is a caving trip, where you need flashlight to enter. Well, after all, it's worth the visit!!!
review 3:
Was really interesting place for stay and enjoy the view, there is a stunning waterfall.

Nice trekking path
Interesting cave
Enjoyable activities
Nice camp

Thank you for all Paras Petanu team for their hospitality....
review 4: I've been going to Paras Petanu and I'd highly recommend it to anyone, especially families. The site is beautiful and the people are warm and welcoming.
review 5: Enjoy the time with best camp ground with a waterfall view.

name: Babi Guling Pak Caek
address: H8J3+23V, Jl. Sentanu, Kedisan, Kec. Tegallalang, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1:
Always wanted to try Balinese local food, especially their famous Suckling Pig (Babi Guling).

However, was let down by the miserable serving of only 1 piece of the skin (see photos) Is this the usual standard?

We did not eat the "intestines or organs" served with the rice and other veggies... ! The bowl of soup or rather thick gravy tasted good tho (is it bamboo shoot or banana stems?)

What is the correct price ? Local 20K and Tourists 40K for the same food but Dual Pricing.. ??
review 2:
Authentic Babi Guling, fresh and flavorful. The soup with baby banana pieces was very delicious and had a kick. My favorite was the crispy pork pieces. Veggies were refreshing and cooked well. It's definitely worth a try if you are in the area. It's also outdoorsy.

Use your hands to eat :)
review 3:
As authentic as we could find
Great food, cutlery containing few stains of previous servings. Food vs price  excellent.

Very friendly staff and great view
review 4:
So we got to this place due to the previous review. And no disappointment at all.
It's a simple side of the road warung, all in good conditions. And an amazing view to the jungle on the side.
And the babi guling oh my God, super tasty. We have had one before and this one was mind blowing. The little soup it's super tasty and all vegetables and pork amazing taste.
We got the same price 40k idr for the little bowl of soup, plate with pork, rice and veggies and drink.
review 5: Found this shop with a little detour on our way to Gunung Batur. Taste delicious, soft and tender but the highlight is the deep fried pork

name: Warung Bambu,local food.
address: Jl. Sentanu, Tampaksiring, Kec. Tampaksiring, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80552, Indonesia

review 2: Excellent Service. The owners are very very friendly! We felt so comfortable. They even gave us one rice for free. They also offer Grab Delivery, which is not very often in this area. The crispy chicken is so delicious!
review 3: Tasty dishes for good prices ‚ò∫Ô∏èüôè we took gado-gado and nasi goreng - owner brought some fruits for compliment üòç thank You so much üòä
review 4:
We ordered on grab chicken soup, chicken satay and fried rice on 08.10.2023. We could only eat the rice. Unfortunately, the tofu was sour, the chicken satay taste was weird.
I won‚Äôt recommend the food after this experience.
review 5: Lovely local place to eat at a very good price. The owner was extreme kind and welcoming and the food is truly homemade and delicious. I really recommend you to pass by and eat there or have a fruit juice.

name: The Jungle Amertha Campsite
address: Jl. Sentanu, Tampaksiring, Kec. Tampaksiring, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1: My partner and I stayed here for two nights, we wish we had of stayed longer. After a long day of travel to Bali this was the perfect start to our trip. Friendly and helpful staff, good food, great massage. This is the place in Bali to truly unwind and relax. There are tours available for day trips but we enjoyed just relaxing at the resort mostly. Would stay again!
